result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Taylor A. Simpson

records.addlTxt:
Sentencing hearing on November 9, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

ALL PARTIES TO THE ACTION SHALL APPEAR IN PERSON FOR THIS HEARING.  THIS HEARING IS NOT BEING HELD VIA ZOOM.

10:27 AM Defendant Taylor A. Simpson in court, in custody.  Attorney Bryant S Plank appeared by video for Taylor A. Simpson.  Attorney Jensen in court for State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a plea of No Contest to Count 1. Remaining charges DRI. 
Court reviewed the elements and potential penalties of the charge the defendant plead to.  She understood.   Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. Felony warnings given.  She understood. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered her plea and waived her constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of Possess w/ Intent-Amphetamine/Methamphetamine/etc.(>10-50g) contrary to 961.41(1m)(e)3. 

Joint recommendation:  Court order PSI. State will recommend prison and cap initial confinement at 7 yrs. 

Court orders PSI, due 10/31. Set sentencing date after 10/31 on a non Monday.  Atty Plank will schedule with JA.
Waive reading of the information.  Defense entered NGP.  Court entered NGP on the defendant's behalf.

10:28 AM Defendant Taylor A. Simpson in court, in custody.  Attorney Bryant S Plank appeared by video for Taylor A. Simpson.  Attorney Jensen in court for State of Wisconsin. Court questioned defendant on her understanding of the waiver of preliminary hearing.  She stated she understood.  Court found that the defendant knowingly and intelligently waived her right to have a preliminary hearing.
